## ğŸ“Š Economic Model

### City Demographics

- **Non-Working**: 30% (children, retired, etc.)
- **Working Age**: 70% of population
- **Employment Rate**: 85% of working age
- **Unemployment**: 15% of working age

### Economic Classes

| Class | Population | Salary Range | Disposable Income |
|-------|-----------|--------------|-------------------|
| Lower | 25% | $20K - $35K | 15% |
| Working | 35% | $35K - $55K | 25% |
| Lower Middle | 25% | $55K - $110K | 35% |
| Upper Middle | 14% | $110K - $375K | 45% |
| Upper | 1% | $375K - $1.5M | 55% |
| Rich | 0.05% | $1.5M - $5M | 65% |

### Salary Calculation
```
Average Salary = Min + (Max - Min) Ã— City Salary Level
```

Where City Salary Level ranges from 0.1 to 1.0

